although the play achieved great renown during its first few years and remained very popular throughout the second half of the 19th century , it is best remembered as the play u.s. president abraham lincoln was attending in ford 's theatre when he was assassinated by actor and confederate sympathizer john wilkes booth on april 14 , 1865 .

